  "texts": [
    "By Theorem 4.2, given ρ ∈ Hom red (π 1 (B), G), the first step in the above decoupling reduces to finding a conformal structure c for which the harmonic map h c is also weakly conformal.",
    "Notice that this holds for some h c if and only if it holds for any, since the action of G on (G/K, g sym) is by isometries.",
    "It turns out that this condition is also sufficient:Theorem 4.3.",
    "If h: ( B2, c) → (G/K, g sym)is a harmonic, ρ-equivariant map, then it is possible to solve (20b) for g B ∈ c if and only if h is weakly conformal.",
    "Moreover, when it exists, such a solution is unique.Proof."
